Subject: [PATCH] Fixed Apache Benchmark tool timeout issue

Description:
Performnace test via Ab_tool getting timeout error for KeepAlive=true in both basic and session auth

Root Cause:

Ab tool is using the HTTP 1.0 version to make the http requests.
BmcWeb is using the HTTP 1.1 version. When ab tool makeing the http
request with keep alive enabled, bmcweb is not closing the connection
request but ab tool is waiting for the connection to close.

Due to that timeout is happaned.

Fix:

Handled to close the keep alive request from HTTP 1.0 version after
the request is completed.

Test Case

Case (1)
>>> Ab_Tool# cat CONFIG
Username=root
Password=0penBmc
IP=10.0.106.193
Nof_iterations=25
UpdateURIs=false
time_out=30
UseSessionAuth=true
KeepAlive=false
>>>> Ab_Tool# ./Ab_Run.sh
381/381 Completed
Finished

Case (2)
>>> Ab_Tool# cat CONFIG
Username=root
Password=0penBmc
IP=10.0.106.193
Nof_iterations=25
UpdateURIs=false
time_out=30
UseSessionAuth=false
KeepAlive=false
>>>> Ab_Tool# ./Ab_Run.sh
381/381 Completed
Finished

Signed-off-by: vamsikrishnak <vamsikrishnak@ami.com>
---
 http/http_connection.hpp | 20 ++++++++++++++++++--
 1 file changed, 18 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/http/http_connection.hpp b/http/http_connection.hpp
index 2d92f0b..057c803 100644
--- a/http/http_connection.hpp
+++ b/http/http_connection.hpp
@@ -479,7 +479,7 @@ class Connection :
             }
 
             doRead();
-            });
+        });
     }
 
     void doRead()
@@ -518,7 +518,7 @@ class Connection :
 
             cancelDeadlineTimer();
             handle();
-            });
+        });
     }
 
     void doWrite(crow::Response& thisRes)
@@ -547,6 +547,22 @@ class Connection :
                 BMCWEB_LOG_DEBUG("{} from write(1)", logPtr(this));
                 return;
             }
+            if (res.keepAlive())
+            {
+                std::error_code reqEc;
+                crow::Request& Req = req.emplace(parser->release(), reqEc);
+                if (reqEc)
+                {
+                    BMCWEB_LOG_DEBUG("Request failed to construct", reqEc.message());
+                    return;
+                }
+                // close the request connection from HTTP 1.0
+                if (Req.version() == 10)
+                {
+                    close();
+                    return;
+                }
+            }
 
             serializer.reset();
             BMCWEB_LOG_DEBUG("{} Clearing response", logPtr(this));
